ion to a host of concerns in feminist theory while applying a gender lens to a wide range of literature and media from the past two centuries. In exploring how individuals and communities might reduce bias and discrimination and ensure gender equity, these fictions serve as both a measure and a means of feminism's progress.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aEquality. 0aFeminismxHistoryy21st century. 0aSex discrimination against women. 0aTelevision and women. 0aWomen in literature. 0aWomenxSocial conditionsy21st century. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Mass Media. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Literary History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849395440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493954423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493954/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles